title: The Sound of Music
overview: A woman leaves an Austrian convent to become a governess to the children of a Naval officer widower.

title: The Last King of Scotland
overview: Based on the events of the brutal Ugandan dictator Idi Amin's regime as seen by his personal physician during the 1970s.

title: The Message
overview: This epic historical drama chronicles the life and times of Prophet Muhammad and serves as an introduction to early Islamic history.

title: The Artist
overview: An egomaniacal film star develops a relationship with a young dancer against the backdrop of Hollywood's silent era.

title: The Wolf of Wall Street
overview: Based on the true story of Jordan Belfort, from his rise to a wealthy stock-broker living the high life to his fall involving crime, corruption and the federal government.

title: A Man for All Seasons
overview: The story of Sir Thomas More, who stood up to King Henry VIII when the King rejected the Roman Catholic Church to obtain a divorce and remarry.

title: The Last Emperor
overview: The story of the final Emperor of China.

title: In the Name of the Father
overview: A man's coerced confession to an I.R.A. bombing he did not commit results in the imprisonment of his father as well. An English lawyer fights to free them.

title: The Shop Around the Corner
overview: Two employees at a gift shop can barely stand each other, without realizing that they are falling in love through the post as each other's anonymous pen pal.

title: The Graduate
overview: A disillusioned college graduate finds himself torn between his older lover and her daughter.

title: The Pursuit of Happyness
overview: A struggling salesman takes custody of his son as he's poised to begin a life-changing professional career.

title: The Hurricane
overview: The story of Rubin 'Hurricane' Carter, a boxer wrongly imprisoned for murder, and the people who aided in his fight to prove his innocence.

title: The Blind Side
overview: The story of Michael Oher, a homeless and traumatized boy who became an All-American football player and first-round NFL draft pick with the help of a caring woman and her family.

title: The Straight Story
overview: An old man makes a long journey by lawnmower to mend his relationship with an ill brother.
stars: ['Richard Farnsworth', 'Sissy Spacek', 'Jane Galloway Heitz', 'Joseph A. Carpenter']

title: The Pianist
overview: A Polish Jewish musician struggles to survive the destruction of the Warsaw ghetto of World War II.

title: The Lion in Winter
overview: 1183 A.D.: King Henry II's three sons all want to inherit the throne, but he won't commit to a choice. They and his wife variously plot to force him.

title: The King's Speech
overview: The story of King George VI, his impromptu ascension to the throne of the British Empire in 1936, and the speech therapist who helped the unsure monarch overcome his stammer.

title: The Imitation Game
overview: During World War II, the English mathematical genius Alan Turing tries to crack the German Enigma code with help from fellow mathematicians.

title: Malcolm X
overview: Biographical epic of the controversial and influential Black Nationalist leader, from his early life and career as a small-time gangster, to his ministry as a member of the Nation of Islam.

title: A Beautiful Mind
overview: After John Nash, a brilliant but asocial mathematician, accepts secret work in cryptography, his life takes a turn for the nightmarish.
